article.headline: Alabama St. 90, Paul Quinn 72
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Brandon Gordon scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Alabama State to a 90-72 win over Paul Quinn College on Saturday. Four other Hornets (1-0) also scored in double figures: Andrew Hayles and Chief Kickingstallionsims with 14 points apiece, Richard Lott with 13 and Joel Bosh with 10. Alabama State held a decisive 55-35 edge in rebounding. Jazz Henderson scored a game-high 21 points for Paul Quinn (0-1), an NAIA school. Damien Chisholm added 19 for Paul Quinn, while Cedric Brooks finished with eight points and 10 rebounds. Paul Quinn struggled from 3-point range, making just 3-of-20. The Hornets made 6-of-16 from beyond the arc. The game was played at SMU's Moody Coliseum as the opener in the school's Tip-Off Classic.
